  "source": "[a \\:strictly.precedes:/ b]\nDescribes: a\nwhen:\n. a, b is \\set\nextends:\n. a is \\set\nsatisfies:\n. allOf:\n  . a \\:precedes:/ b\n  . not:\n    . a = b\nDocumented:\n. called: \"strictly precedes\"\n. written: \"a? \\prec b?\"\n. description: \"For elements of a partially ordered set, $a \\prec b$ means $a \\preceq b$ and $a \\neq b$. The relation $\\prec$ is transitive, and $a \\prec b$ implies $b \\not\\preceq a$.\"\nId: \"27072d67-4964-456d-8a5b-1c526dff5ae0\"",
